There are several web-based Base64 encoders/decoders, and only a couple Javascript encoders/decoders. The Javascript ones were all 
rather complex (relatively speaking), and none used the functions for working with Base64 that are built into the JavaScript engine in 
Netscape Communicator 4,x and up, and Mozilla. This uses those built in functions, and so it doesn't work in Internet Explorer, or 
Opera. 






